<DOC><DOCNO> AP880513-0078 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-13-88 0831EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-Dominican-Embezzle     05-13 0299</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Dominican-Embezzle,0308</SECOND><HEAD>Lawmaker Convicted Of Embezzlement, Fined $3 Million</HEAD><DATELINE>SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A former aide toex-President Salvador Jorge Blanco has been fined $3 million andsentenced to nine months in jail for embezzling $85,000.   Rafael Flores Estrella, a member of the Chamber of Deputies andBlanco's former administrative assistant, was sentenced followinghis conviction Thursday night by the Supreme Court.   He is one of nearly 20 former government officials, includingJorge Blanco, accused of widespread corruption that allegedlyoccurred during the former president's administration. Estrella wasthe first to stand trial.   Flores Estrella was tried by the Supreme Court because he is amember of the legislature, a post he automatically loses because ofhis conviction.   He was charged with taking $85,000 from the treasury for a 1985trip that Jorge Blanco was to make to Panama and Costa Rica.Prosecutors alleged the trip was never taken and the money neverwas returned.   Flores Estrella denied any wrongdoing.   The court stipulated that one day would be added to his jailterm for each dollar of the $3 million fine that Flores Estrelladoes not pay.   Jorge Blanco and other officials are accused of misusinggovernment funds to buy military equipment at inflated prices andembezzling money earmarked for a public food program.   Jorge Blanco, president from 1982 to 1986, has said the chargesare politically motivated. The corruption probe was ordered bycurrent President Joaquin Balaguer after he took office.   The former chief executive was allowed to leave Santo Domingo ayear ago for treatment of a heart ailment at Emory UniversityHospital in Atlanta.   Jorge Blanco has ignored an order to return home and thegovernment has not attempted to extradite him. He is expected to betried regardless of whether he returns.</TEXT></DOC>